<subSubSection id="5CC1F432AC1671B77177D360AF1A567F" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="EEDE86B7EF29CC943733A35822FD16D9" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1DC9EC6056302341FD25DE70D33BE86" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="47669F84B7597CAEEBA808B341D663A6" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Radomaniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Radomaniola" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Radomaniola</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="E2FA4AC7E9FAF3D8C79B73951B25DD3B" author="Szarowska, M" journalOrPublisher="Folia Malacologica" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="99 - 168" title="Molecular phylogeny, systematics and morphological character evolution in the balkan Rissooidea (Caenogastropoda)." volume="14" year="2006">Szarowska (2006)</bibRefCitation>
as a replacement name for the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C30FA367EC8A1EC359B838E89981C33" genus="Orientalina" lsidName="Orientalina" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="genus">Orientalina</taxonomicName>
(Radoman, 1978). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="2AA9AB47F502243E515757068F6B1F04" author="Radoman, P" journalOrPublisher="Department of Sciences" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" title="Hydrobioidea, a Superfamily of Prosobranchia (Gastropoda)" volumeTitle="Monographs DXLVII" year="1983">Radoman (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, the Balkan species 
<taxonomicName id="20C73B05F0C83504E6244061EC944CE8" genus="Orientalina" lsidName="Orientalina curta" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species" species="curta">Orientalina curta</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="1BA53C42F4A481FDDCFCF2B5EAA770F8" originalValue="Küster">Kuester</normalizedToken>
, 1852) may be divided into a few subspecies on the basis of shell properties and the same author reported the presence of the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="3A056EB70D31AB370B14D3EF0038459D" genus="Orientalina" lsidName="Orientalina curta subsp. albanica" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="subSpecies" species="curta" subSpecies="albanica">Orientalina curta albanica</taxonomicName>
Radoman, 1973 from the area of Ioannina. However, the shell dimensions of the specimens we collected from localities of Aitoloakarnania and Ioannina, (shell height: 1.90-3.65 mm, shell width: 1.20-1.95 mm, aperture height: 0.85-1.30 mm, aperture width: 0.70-1.20 mm) are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="F20CA6519E516D7F3A49862A248872C7" genus="Orientalina" lsidName="Orientalina curta subsp. curta" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="subSpecies" species="curta" subSpecies="curta">Orientalina curta curta</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="21F4DC6693F01FDE716DB08596262F3A" originalValue="Küster">Kuester</normalizedToken>
, 1852) (shell height: 2.31-3.23 mm, shell width: 1.39-1.93 mm, aperture height: 0.92-1.30 mm, aperture width: 0.84-1.18 mm) reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="698255BF483B4540187397420A1EE7DB" author="Radoman, P" journalOrPublisher="Department of Sciences" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" title="Hydrobioidea, a Superfamily of Prosobranchia (Gastropoda)" volumeTitle="Monographs DXLVII" year="1983">Radoman (1983)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D7EA2018FEDBEAF618A490ED7C45DA3" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="B6BBBF1BCB3A8300AFB49C3F13B7565C" author="Falniowski, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="19 - 36" title="Molecules vs morphology in the taxonomy of the Radomaniola / Grossuana group of balkan Rissooidea (Mollusca, Caenogastropoda)." url="10.2478/v10125-012-0006-2" volume="41" year="2012">Falniowski et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
analyzed molecular data from populations of the 
<taxonomicName id="C581EBDC14A1D9AB116911F19B57B75A" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Radomaniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Radomaniola" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<pageBreakToken id="7F372873281A3DBEA3BF2E8F2E52654C" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" start="start">Radomaniola</pageBreakToken>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="D2B004E24DD9344BA5F5BB0B523AB00E" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Grossuana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Grossuana" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Grossuana</taxonomicName>
group collected from several localities of Greece and other countries of Balkan Peninsula. Two of the Greek localities were &quot;spring in the city centre of Thermos, NE of Trichonida Lake&quot; and &quot;springs of Louros&quot;. In the Bayesian tree based on COI sequences provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="68322436B801D0DFBB2C0165939A9B15" author="Falniowski, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="19 - 36" title="Molecules vs morphology in the taxonomy of the Radomaniola / Grossuana group of balkan Rissooidea (Mollusca, Caenogastropoda)." url="10.2478/v10125-012-0006-2" volume="41" year="2012">Falniowski et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, the specimens from these localities belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="622151A6F850951C4F55818B69754F63" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Radomaniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Radomaniola" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Radomaniola</taxonomicName>
s. stricto. The above authors refer to the specimens from Thermos as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="F36D447472BA985B5452DB8F4041441F" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Trichonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trichonia kephalovrissonia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kephalovrissonia">Trichonia kephalovrissonia</taxonomicName>
&quot; in the Bayesian tree. This fact indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="A0AF6FABF1FB2463CC50EC29714EEAB3" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Trichonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trichonia kephalovrissonia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kephalovrissonia">Trichonia kephalovrissonia</taxonomicName>
Radoman, 1973 [
<bibRefCitation id="40F37AB5C31D343BD64C58962BAAEB89" author="Schuett, H" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="115 - 149" title="Zur Kenntnis griechischer Hydrobiiden." volume="110" year="1980">
<normalizedToken id="B6EF1A36351383A53AF188FB52F6F057" originalValue="Schütt">Schuett</normalizedToken>
(1980)
</bibRefCitation>
considers this taxon as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="13463FB9FCF2820C31D706C49371404F" authority="Radoman, 1974" authorityName="Radoman" authorityYear="1974" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochliopidae" genus="Semisalsa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Semisalsa steindachneri" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="steindachneri">Semisalsa steindachneri</taxonomicName>
(Westerlund, 1902) (= 
<taxonomicName id="7DE56CD8D87E11146F053ED59C96B8E1" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochliopidae" genus="Heleobia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heleobia (Semisalsa) steindachneri" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="steindachneri" subGenus="Semisalsa">Heleobia (Semisalsa) steindachneri</taxonomicName>
(Westerlund, 1902)] should be assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E253A3F5B60AF3F9372FA661BB7B3" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Radomaniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Radomaniola kephalovrissonia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kephalovrissonia">Radomaniola kephalovrissonia</taxonomicName>
(Radoman, 1973). In the Bayesian tree mentioned above, the specimens from Louros seem to be close to 
<taxonomicName id="80413EEBF510B57B9E43EA961AC732E0" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Radomaniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Radomaniola montana" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="montana">Radomaniola montana</taxonomicName>
(Radoman, 1973) and rather far from 
<taxonomicName id="0D52FA9400552581C168CDC59C4246C2" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Radomaniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Radomaniola curta subsp. curta" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="curta" subSpecies="curta">Radomaniola curta curta</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="D74AB51BD25C0FD515AFC4F0C82C1DA3" originalValue="Küster">Kuester</normalizedToken>
, 1852) and other 
<taxonomicName id="0FB25202395554850DAE4E287DB1E723" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Radomaniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Radomaniola curta" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="curta">Radomaniola curta</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="E42669635051A5D1F4B6E90420AFB30A" originalValue="Küster">Kuester</normalizedToken>
, 1852) subspecies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="578C3A8321DE0D557E07EA1112C07C02" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Despite the fact that our sampling localities (Fig. 1) are situated very close to those of 
<bibRefCitation id="5B5478176C86253F35DE06FB982076E7" author="Falniowski, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="19 - 36" title="Molecules vs morphology in the taxonomy of the Radomaniola / Grossuana group of balkan Rissooidea (Mollusca, Caenogastropoda)." url="10.2478/v10125-012-0006-2" volume="41" year="2012">Falniowski et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, we consider that all specimens collected from Aitoloakarnania and Ioannina belong to 
<taxonomicName id="E6EEDE73D7C3568F3271605ABA7E2DD3" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Radomaniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Radomaniola curta" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="curta">Radomaniola curta</taxonomicName>
as long as only their morphological and anatomical characters have been examined and no molecular data are available.
</paragraph>
